observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the
LCE agreed to instruct the
(a) Municipal Treasurer
to:
(i) forward the Certified List of Taxpayers to the Accounting Office;
(ii) prepare the data necessary in the computation of the RPT Target Collections based on the formula provided by the BLGF;
(iii) make representations for the deployment of support staff to assist in the documentation and collection of tax delinquencies;
(iv) recommend for the filing of legal actions that auction be conducted for against the tax delinquents;
(v) propose for the funding of the preparation of cadastral map that would be used in tax mapping; and
(vi) strategize on how to maximize tax collections; and
(b) Municipal Accountant to:
(i) ensure that balances recorded to set up the receivables are based on the updated RPTAR/TIC; and
(ii) initiate the reconciliation of Accounting and MTO records and to affect necessary adjustment, if any.

We recommend that the management:

comply strictly with COA Circular No. 97-002 in the granting of cash advances and the subsequent liquidations thereof;  

closely monitor the movement of the cash advances;  


continue to send demand letters officers and employees to immediately settle their unliquidated cash advances; 



adopt legal measure for collection or refund of cash advances should the concerned personnel failed to settle their accounts; and 


if efforts exerted become futile, management should secure an authority from the COA to write off of the subject dormant accounts supported by the requirements prescribed in COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to:

continue its satisfactory management of its 20% Development Fund;



instruct the project proponent and the Municipal Budget Officer to ensure that proposed PPAs are adequately funded prior to their approval and inclusion in the Annual Procurement Plan; 


Municipal Planning and Development Officer and Municipal Engineer to see to it that approved PPAs are timely implemented; and


Local Development Council and the Municipal Budget Officer in coordination with the Sangguniang Bayan to closely scrutinize the nature of charges proposed under the 20% DF to ensure compliance with the requirement of Section 2.3 of the DILG-DMB JMC No. 2017-01.

We recommended and the Management agreed that the Local Chief Executive instruct the 
Municipal Treasurer to (i) submit to the Municipal Accountant a duly certified list showing the name of the taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year 2018; and 
(ii) coordinate with the Municipal Assessor and Municipal Accountant for the determination of uncollected RPT and SET incomes of prior years in accordance with the prescribed procedures; 
Municipal Accountant to (i) set up RPT and SET Receivables for each year corresponding to the lists and make necessary adjustments as warranted; 
and (ii) henceforth observe the prescribed accounting procedures in recording RPT and SET receivables and incomes.

We recommended and the Management concurred to:

(a) exert serious efforts in locating the titles of the other lands listed in the Summary of Owned Lands provided by the Office of the Assessor; 

(b) take immediate action to ensure that the immediate registration and titling of the subject parcels of land in the name of the municipality are undertaken; 

(c) allocate funds for incidental expenses to be incurred in the registration of titles; and 

(d) reconcile the records and documents of the Offices of Accounting, Treasurer and Assessor regularly to ascertain that the balance recorded in the books of the LGU is valid and accurate.

a. require Municipal Treasurer to furnish the Municipal Accountant a duly signed certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible every beginning of the year for recording purposes; 

b.	instruct the Municipal Accountant to draw a JEV to record the RPT/SET receivables based on the certified list from the Office of the City Treasurer and ensure that the recorded receivables are based on actual reference documents;

c.	encourage the involvement of barangay officials in the tax campaign to reach out to a larger area; and 

d.	intensify tax collections thru formulating strategies to improve collection of real property taxes.

(a) secure the approved copy of the Ten-Year Solid Waste Management Plan; 

(b) provide a specific budget for the Solid Waste Programs and Activities;

(c) coordinate with the Sangguniang Bayan for the enactment and passage of Municipal Ordinances that would enforce the implementation of the five basic environmental laws on the preservation and protection of the environment required under R.A. No. 9003.

We recommended that the management:
comply strictly with COA Circular No. 97-002 in the granting of cash advances and the subsequent liquidations thereof;
ensure that the necessary supporting documents pertaining to the cash advances are complete;
closely monitor the movement of the cash advances; and
demand officers and employees to immediately settle their unliquidated cash advances.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
require Municipal Treasurer to furnish the Municipal Accountant a duly signed certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible every beginning of the year for recording purposes;
instruct the Municipal Accountant to draw a JEV to record the RPT/SET receivables based on the certified list from the Office of the City Treasurer and ensure that the recorded receivables are based on actual reference documents;
encourage the involvement of barangay officials in the tax campaign to reach out to a larger area; and
intensify tax collections thru formulating strategies to improve collection of real property taxes.
